e external ears (sharper directionality). The importance of IIDs for lateralization and horizontal localization is discussed by comparing the behavioural directional performance of bats with their bioacoustical features.", "access_right": "open", "creators": [{"name": "Obrist, Martin K.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fenton, M. Brock", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Eger, Judith L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Schlegel, Peter A.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/fa48067b7c8996758319c7d068a7c9af", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/3a7a35551b648e8410caf5b102bc381ae1826add425d53d51e031ce48b547057", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/Z64VZUIQ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/Z64VZUIQ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/dffe0e214451660ff7303350efa17263!/b109168-111722", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1", "pages": "119-152", "title": "Journal of Experimental Biology", "volume": "180"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/fa48067b7c8996758319c7d068a7c9af"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:Z64VZUIQ"}, {"identifier": "10.1242/jeb.180.1.119"}], "license": {"id": "cc-by-4.0"}, "communities": [